-- Super Bowl Is Most-Watched U.S. TV Event
-- B y   M a s o n   L e v i n s o n
-- 2012-02-06T19:59:23Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-06/giants-super-bowl-win-over-patriots-is-most-watched-u-s-television-event.html
The  New York Giants ’ victory over the
 New England Patriots  in last night’s Super Bowl drew the largest
audience in U.S. television history,  Comcast Corp. (CMCSA) ’s NBC network
said.  The Giants’ 21-17 win drew an audience of 111.3 million
viewers, topping the record of 111 million set by last year’s
Super Bowl between Pittsburgh and  Green Bay .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Larry Siddons at 
 lsiddons@bloomberg.net  